&lt;p&gt;AXS is seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Sr. Software Engineer II - Full Stack&lt;/strong&gt; to contribute to the design and development of core ticketing platforms. This role is ideal for an engineer who thrives in a complex enterprise environment and is comfortable working across modern web technologies, services, APIs, and integrations in support of high-demand, global use cases.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will build and scale consumer-facing and B2B web applications, with ownership across front-end experiences, back-end services, and data integrations. You will partner closely with product, design, and engineering teams to deliver reliable, high-quality web experiences while helping shape technical decisions and improve the platform over time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a senior individual contributor, you will contribute hands-on to implementation while also influencing architecture, guiding technical direction within your team, and helping drive alignment between engineering efforts and business goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Be Doing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a deep domain expert and go-to engineer in a critical area of the platform.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead technically complex initiatives from design through delivery, ensuring scalability, reliability, and performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design cross-team solutions and influence architecture and technical direction across the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own features and systems end-to-end, including technical design, implementation, testing, and production support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and evolve scalable, maintainable, and high-performing web experiences for global ticketing platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Product, Design, and engineering stakeholders to deliver intuitive, accessible, and responsive customer-facing applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply full-stack engineering best practices across service design, API contracts, component architecture, performance optimization, accessibility, testing, and maintainability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build scalable modules for internal applications and external partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and evolve services and APIs that power mission-critical infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify and implement improvements in performance, stability, maintainability, process, and tooling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in design and code reviews to ensure best practices and high-quality code.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate effectively with architects, engineers, business analysts, product managers, and project managers to deliver innovative solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor and guide engineers across multiple teams, contributing to technical growth and engineering excellence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with third parties and security stakeholders as needed to deliver integrated and secure solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
